Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.NutritionIntake` for use in FHIR R4

Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-NutritionIntake Version: 0.0.1-snapshot-3
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-21 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionNutritionIntake

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element NutritionIntake for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Basic

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • Use this Extension: Cross-version Profile for R5.NutritionIntake for use in FHIR R4

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element NutritionIntake for use in FHIR R4.

  • instantiatesCanonical: canonical: Instantiates FHIR protocol or definition.
  • instantiatesUri: uri: Instantiates external protocol or definition.
  • basedOn: Reference: A plan, proposal or order that is fulfilled in whole or in part by this event.
  • partOf: Reference: A larger event of which this particular event is a component or step.
  • status: code: A code representing the patient or other source's judgment about the state of the intake that this assertion is about. Generally, this will be active or completed.
  • statusReason: CodeableConcept: Captures the reason for the current state of the NutritionIntake.
  • code: CodeableConcept: Overall type of nutrition intake.
  • encounter: Reference: The encounter that establishes the context for this NutritionIntake.
  • occurrence: dateTime, Period: The interval of time during which it is being asserted that the patient is/was consuming the food or fluid.
  • recorded: dateTime: The date when the Nutrition Intake was asserted by the information source.
  • reported: boolean, Reference: The person or organization that provided the information about the consumption of this food or fluid. Note: Use derivedFrom when a NutritionIntake is derived from other resources.
  • type: CodeableConcept: Indicates what a category of item that was consumed: e.g., food, fluid, enteral, etc.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • schedule: Timing: Scheduled frequency of consumption.
  • amount: Quantity: Quantity of the specified food.
  • rate: Quantity: Rate at which enteral feeding was administered.
  • notConsumed: boolean: Indicator when a patient is in a setting where it is helpful to know if food was not consumed, such as it was refused, held (as in tube feedings), or otherwise not provided. If a consumption is being recorded from an app, such as MyFitnessPal, this indicator will likely not be used.
  • notConsumedReason: CodeableConcept: Document the reason the food or fluid was not consumed, such as refused, held, etc.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • amount: Quantity: Total amount of nutrient consumed.
  • function: CodeableConcept: Type of performer.
  • actor: Reference: Who performed the intake.
  • location: Reference: Where the intake occurred.
  • derivedFrom: Reference: Allows linking the NutritionIntake to the underlying NutritionOrder, or to other information, such as AllergyIntolerance, that supports or is used to derive the NutritionIntake.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • note: Annotation: Provides extra information about the Nutrition Intake that is not conveyed by the other attributes.

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element NutritionIntake for use in FHIR R4.

  • instantiatesCanonical: canonical: Instantiates FHIR protocol or definition.
  • instantiatesUri: uri: Instantiates external protocol or definition.
  • basedOn: Reference: A plan, proposal or order that is fulfilled in whole or in part by this event.
  • partOf: Reference: A larger event of which this particular event is a component or step.
  • status: code: A code representing the patient or other source's judgment about the state of the intake that this assertion is about. Generally, this will be active or completed.
  • statusReason: CodeableConcept: Captures the reason for the current state of the NutritionIntake.
  • code: CodeableConcept: Overall type of nutrition intake.
  • encounter: Reference: The encounter that establishes the context for this NutritionIntake.
  • occurrence: dateTime, Period: The interval of time during which it is being asserted that the patient is/was consuming the food or fluid.
  • recorded: dateTime: The date when the Nutrition Intake was asserted by the information source.
  • reported: boolean, Reference: The person or organization that provided the information about the consumption of this food or fluid. Note: Use derivedFrom when a NutritionIntake is derived from other resources.
  • type: CodeableConcept: Indicates what a category of item that was consumed: e.g., food, fluid, enteral, etc.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • schedule: Timing: Scheduled frequency of consumption.
  • amount: Quantity: Quantity of the specified food.
  • rate: Quantity: Rate at which enteral feeding was administered.
  • notConsumed: boolean: Indicator when a patient is in a setting where it is helpful to know if food was not consumed, such as it was refused, held (as in tube feedings), or otherwise not provided. If a consumption is being recorded from an app, such as MyFitnessPal, this indicator will likely not be used.
  • notConsumedReason: CodeableConcept: Document the reason the food or fluid was not consumed, such as refused, held, etc.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • amount: Quantity: Total amount of nutrient consumed.
  • function: CodeableConcept: Type of performer.
  • actor: Reference: Who performed the intake.
  • location: Reference: Where the intake occurred.
  • derivedFrom: Reference: Allows linking the NutritionIntake to the underlying NutritionOrder, or to other information, such as AllergyIntolerance, that supports or is used to derive the NutritionIntake.
  • _datatype: string: Slice to indicate the presence of a R5 CodeableReference in FHIR R4
  • concept: CodeableConcept: A reference to a concept - e.g. the information is identified by its general class to the degree of precision found in the terminology.
  • reference: Reference: A reference to a resource the provides exact details about the information being referenced.
  • note: Annotation: Provides extra information about the Nutrition Intake that is not conveyed by the other attributes.
